{{As of|2022|pre=the}} [[American Community Survey]] estimates, there were {{formatnum:1748}} people and {{formatnum:798}} households.<ref name=DP02>{{cite web|url=https://data.census.gov/table/ACSDP5Y2022.DP02?g=160XX00US4262128 | title= 2022 American Community Survey 5 Year Estimate: Selected Social Characteristics in the United States for Port Carbon borough, PA | access-date = 2024-06-21 | publisher = [[United States Census Bureau]]}}</ref><ref name=DP05>{{cite web|url=https://data.census.gov/table/ACSDP5Y2022.DP05?g=160XX00US4262128 | title= 2022 American Community Survey 5 Year Estimate: Demographic and Housing Estimates for Port Carbon borough, PA | access-date = 2024-06-21 | publisher = [[United States Census Bureau]]}}</ref> The [[population density]] was {{convert|2318.3|PD/sqmi|PD/km2|1}}. There were {{formatnum:877}} housing units at an average density of {{convert|1163.1|/sqmi|/km2|1}}.<ref name=B25001>{{cite web|url=https://data.census.gov/table/ACSDT5Y2022.B25001?g=160XX00US4262128 | title= 2022 American Community Survey 5 Year Estimate: Housing Units for Port Carbon borough, PA | access-date = 2024-06-21 | publisher = [[United States Census Bureau]]}}</ref><ref name=Gaz2023>To calculate density we use the land area figure from the places file in {{cite web| url=https://www.census.gov/geographies/reference-files/time-series/geo/gazetteer-files.html | title = The 2023 U.S. Gazetteer Files}}</ref><ref name=DP05/> The racial makeup of the city was 92.7%&nbsp;White, 2.7%&nbsp;Black or African American, 2.2%&nbsp;some other race, and 0.5%&nbsp;Asian, with 1.9%&nbsp;from two or more races.<ref name=DP05/> [[Hispanic and Latino Americans|Hispanics or Latinos]] of any race were 2.3%&nbsp;of the population.<ref name=DP05/>

Of the {{formatnum:798}} households, 21.9%&nbsp;had children under the age of 18 living with them, 42.0%&nbsp;had seniors 65 years or older living with them, 48.9%&nbsp;were married couples living together, 8.6%&nbsp;were couples cohabitating, 21.4%&nbsp;had a male householder with no partner present, and 21.1%&nbsp;had a female householder with no partner present.<ref name=DP02/> The median household size was {{formatnum:2.19}} and the median family size was {{formatnum:2.89}}.<ref name=DP02/>

The age distribution was 18.3%&nbsp;under 18, 4.6%&nbsp;from 18 to 24, 23.3%&nbsp;from 25 to 44, 29.9%&nbsp;from 45 to 64, and 23.8%&nbsp;who were 65 or older. The median age was {{formatnum:48.4}} years.<ref name=S0101>{{cite web|url=https://data.census.gov/table/ACSST5Y2022.S0101?g=160XX00US4262128 | title= 2022 American Community Survey 5 Year Estimate: Age and Sex for Port Carbon borough, PA | access-date = 2024-06-21 | publisher = [[United States Census Bureau]]}}</ref> For every 100 females, there were {{formatnum:93.4}} males.<ref name=DP05/>

The median income for a household was ${{formatnum:54706}}, with family households having a median income of ${{formatnum:68839}} and non-family households ${{formatnum:34805}}. The [[per capita income]] was ${{formatnum:28989}}.<ref name=S1901>{{cite web|url=https://data.census.gov/table/ACSST5Y2022.S1901?g=160XX00US4262128 | title= 2022 American Community Survey 5 Year Estimate: Income in the Past 12 Months (in 2022 Inflation-Adjusted Dollars) for Port Carbon borough, PA | access-date = 2024-06-21 | publisher = [[United States Census Bureau]]}}</ref><ref name=S1902>{{cite web|url=https://data.census.gov/table/ACSST5Y2022.S1902?g=160XX00US4262128 | title= 2022 American Community Survey 5 Year Estimate: Mean Income in the Past 12 Months (in 2022 Inflation-Adjusted Dollars) for Port Carbon borough, PA | access-date = 2024-06-21 | publisher = [[United States Census Bureau]]}}</ref> Out of the {{formatnum:1748}} people with a determined poverty status, 7.6%&nbsp;were below the [[poverty line]]. Further, 0.9%&nbsp;of minors and 8.7%&nbsp;of seniors were below the poverty line.<ref name=S1701>{{cite web|url=https://data.census.gov/table/ACSST5Y2022.S1701?g=160XX00US4262128 | title= 2022 American Community Survey 5 Year Estimate: Poverty Status in the Past 12 Months for Port Carbon borough, PA | access-date = 2024-06-21 | publisher = [[United States Census Bureau]]}}</ref>

In the survey, residents self-identified with various ethnic ancestries. People of [[German American|German]] descent made up 19.6%&nbsp;of the population of the town, followed by [[Irish American|Irish]] at 18.4%, [[Polish American|Polish]] at 11.6%, [[Italian American|Italian]] at 9.6%, [[Lithuanian American|Lithuanian]] at 5.4%, [[Slovak American|Slovak]] at 4.9%, [[Ukrainian American|Ukrainian]] at 3.4%, [[American ancestry|American]] at 3.3%, [[Welsh American|Welsh]] at 2.9%, [[Dutch American|Dutch]] at 1.9%, [[English American|English]] at 1.7%, [[Arab American|Arab]] at 1.1%, [[Scottish American|Scottish]] at 0.9%, [[Sub-Saharan Africa]]n at 0.7%, and [[French American|French]] at 0.6%.<ref name=DP02/>
